{"TopicId":215095,"ForumId":139,"TopicTitle":"Patch One is Go","CreatedByName":"Nate Simpson","CreatedById":205123,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-16T17:00:00Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T00:55:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679013622\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212979\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gussi111\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, gussi111 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell if they stay consistent with updates as big as this one is every few weeks then I expect most people to be happy pretty soon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow\u0027s that award-winning copy treating you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T01:00:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason planes just spontaneously cease to exist during sharp turns in this version lol.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbalServer.com","CreatedById":227836,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T01:12:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EThanks for fixing the \u0022m\u0022 key within the \u003C/b\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022font-weight:bold;\u0022 title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cb\u003E.\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EIt was a bit difficult to build \u0022m k2\u0022 vessels.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E scroll, view, and view movability is also much easier and responsive.\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003ELooking forward to future updates!\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EThanks KSP team!\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-17T01:19:47Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2023 01:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by KerbalServer.com\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EWent into the VAB.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T01:13:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224259612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678986000\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EFix for engine thrust being deflected at too high of a value when a part obstructs an engine\u2019s exhaust\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cb\u003E (the Kraken Drive bug)\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven that this is basically kerbal canon, do you think\u00A0 you could maybe un-fix this? It\u0027s like 30% of youtube videos about this game for the last 10 years\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MARL_Mk1","CreatedById":192535,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T01:33:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat could be causing this?\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nMoving your wings along the longitudinal axis will change how your wings Pitch Up/Down, no matter what you tell the vehicle to do...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/w63rcs8ADlY?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 - Inverted control surfaces Bug\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T01:54:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260739\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679016790\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192535\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MARL_Mk1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, MARL_Mk1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat could be causing this?\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nMoving your wings along the longitudinal axis will change how your wings Pitch Up/Down, no matter what you tell the vehicle to do...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP 1, control surfaces flip direction when the rotation axis of the part changes between ahead of and behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, you really don\u0027t want those wing surfaces to respond to pitch inputs. Since there\u0027s not much lever arm that close to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E, they\u0027re not doing much other than acting as airbrakes. I\u0027ve done enough fighter competitions to know that it will give you slightly better turn performance at the cost of a lot of speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MARL_Mk1","CreatedById":192535,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T03:05:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260754\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679018043\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FleshJeb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, FleshJeb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP 1, control surfaces flip direction when the rotation axis of the part changes between ahead of and behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, you really don\u0027t want those wing surfaces to respond to pitch inputs. Since there\u0027s not much lever arm that close to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, they\u0027re not doing much other than acting as airbrakes. I\u0027ve done enough fighter competitions to know that it will give you slightly better turn performance at the cost of a lot of speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want them to work as I fancy. I like to pitch with them. It\u0027s KSP after all.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nProblem is, I can\u0027t just invert it, because roll, which works fine, gets inverted too, and completely messes up controls even more...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T06:59:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260410\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678999107\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203390\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yakez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Yakez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny timeline on Borderless Window being working feature? Game do not really work with multiple monitor setups... like at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can force many Unity games to do borderless window, also works for KSP2;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pcgamingwiki.com/wiki/Kerbal_Space_Program_2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.pcgamingwiki.com/wiki/Kerbal_Space_Program_2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#333333;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003EThe option is there but acts as exclusive fullscreen.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Csup style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#333333;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pcgamingwiki.com/wiki/Kerbal_Space_Program_2#cite_note-7\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0645ad;\u0022\u003E[5]\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#333333;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EEnabled windowed mode and use\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022border:1px solid #a4bfd6;color:#133562;font-size:13px;padding:0px 1px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E-popupwindow\u003C/code\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#333333;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eas a\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.pcgamingwiki.com/wiki/Glossary:Command_line_arguments\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0645ad;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022 title=\u0022Glossary:Command line arguments\u0022\u003Ecommand line argument\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#333333;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eto switch to borderless windowed.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022d88097a3-600f-4f2c-9f4f-bd8501efc1ae.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022708\u0022 width=\u0022944\u0022 src=\u0022https://thumbs-eu-west-1.myalbum.io/photo/1k0/d88097a3-600f-4f2c-9f4f-bd8501efc1ae.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-17T06:59:24Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2023 06:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by LoSBoL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Navoan","CreatedById":133765,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T07:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan already see the positivity coming out in the comments. Looks like the team has fixed the most pressing bugs (loss of mission), can\u0027t wait to test it out.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"yipyop","CreatedById":226997,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T08:54:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find this patch very encouraging for the future. The three weeks must have been intensive but the result is there, noticeable. The road will be long but the base will get stronger with your efforts...and the coming additions will be even more stimulating.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCourage to the little hand behind the screens...\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd to those who work to make KSP2 a real 2 in the making...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T09:19:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260492\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679004067\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198861\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pmborg\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, pmborg said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E100FPS in 4K\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow. What CPU/GPU combination?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T14:17:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260727\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679015602\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven that this is basically kerbal canon, do you think\u00A0 you could maybe un-fix this? It\u0027s like 30% of youtube videos about this game for the last 10 years\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour comment made me realize something:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224259612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678986000\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nate Simpson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Nate Simpson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cb\u003EFix for engine thrust being deflected at too high of a value when a part obstructs an engine\u2019s exhaust\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cb\u003E (the Kraken Drive bug)\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe thrust got deflected backwards (and I\u0027m assuming there was some funky math on how much thrust should be applied based on where the deflecting surface is), does this mean there is functionality for directing thrust by bouncing it off of surfaces of the craft? I can\u0027t test it myself, but that opens some interesting possibilities if so.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbalRez","CreatedById":227947,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T15:07:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease let us rebind the Aero GUI (default is F12). This interferes with the Steam screenshot default button.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SeanStenson95","CreatedById":227954,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T16:57:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPatch one broke my game. One of two things happen:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) The game fails to load to main menu and a secondary window with the ksp2 logo opens then crashes game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) The game gets to main menu but crashes when I attempt to load a campaign file or create a new campaign. Secondary ksp2 window with logo also appears here before the crash.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttempts at solution:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have attempted to verify integrity of files via Steam, uninstalled/reinstalled ksp2, updated steam. None have worked so far. I do not have any mods installed, nor have I altered any files.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KincaidFrankMF","CreatedById":200426,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T18:31:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224261133\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679072251\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SeanStenson95\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SeanStenson95 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPatch one broke my game. One of two things happen:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) The game fails to load to main menu and a secondary window with the ksp2 logo opens then crashes game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) The game gets to main menu but crashes when I attempt to load a campaign file or create a new campaign. Secondary ksp2 window with logo also appears here before the crash.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttempts at solution:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have attempted to verify integrity of files via Steam, uninstalled/reinstalled ksp2, updated steam. None have worked so far. I do not have any mods installed, nor have I altered any files.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had a similar problem, resolved when I a) updated graphics driver and b) deleted all my old save games\u00A0 (under C drive-\u0026gt;users-\u0026gt;[your name]-\u0026gt;AppData-\u0026gt;LocalLow-\u0026gt;Intercept Games-\u0026gt;Kerbal Space Program 2).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure which of those actually solved it, but suspect it was the second one. Hope that helps!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pmborg","CreatedById":198861,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T19:24:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224260908\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679044782\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow. What CPU/GPU combination?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will post here the detail HW also posted in other posts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDetailed Hardware: \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EThe computer is \u003Cstrong\u003E1.5 years old\u003C/strong\u003E with an RTX4080 upgrade.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- TOWER: \u003C/strong\u003EFRACTAL DESIGN Focus G Black\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- \u003Cstrong\u003EPOWER: \u003C/strong\u003EGIGABYTE P850GM 850W 80 Plus Gold Modular (Recommended to use with RTX 4080)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- Motherboard Model: \u003C/strong\u003EGigabyte X570 AORUS MASTER\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- RAM: \u003C/strong\u003ECRUCIAL Ballistix 32GB 2X16GB DDR4 36000MHz CL16 Red (Recommended Model to use with AMD Processor)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- Processor Name: \u003C/strong\u003EAMD Ryzen 9 5900X 12-Core Processor AM4BOX\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- CPU COOLER: \u003C/strong\u003ENOCTUA NH-D15S Chromax Black\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- GRAPHICS CARD: \u003C/strong\u003EGIGABYTE GeForce RTX 4080 GAMING OC 16GB GDDR6X\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- WIN DRIVE: \u003C/strong\u003EGigabyte ssd aorus 1tb m2 gen4-nvme\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- KSP DRIVE: \u003C/strong\u003ESSD WESTERN DIGITAL SN850 2TB M.2 2280 Black NVMe Gen4 (Word Class M2 SSD)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E- 3x Monitor: \u003C/strong\u003EDELL S2721QS IPS 4ms 27\u2033 4K UHD 16:9 FreeSync\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNOTE: The BIOS settings are very important to allow CPU to boost on single thread application.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe Kerbal Space Program 2 - Settings:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/iZVBphwlFO4?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Kerbal Space Program 2 - My Recommend Settings for 4K resolution\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Os87hrt.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Os87hrt.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe quality of the image is still excellent!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-17T19:33:00Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2023 07:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by pmborg\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T19:32:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed that there\u0027s a survey available in the launcher, might be worth letting more people know, what\u0027d ya think \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022225122\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/225122-dakota/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dakota\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pmborg","CreatedById":198861,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T19:43:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I changed to Full HD resolution I was puzzled with image being generated in 2 monitors...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis patch is better but still a long road ahead \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HMMhlZU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022225\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HMMhlZU.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorst than that is the mouse, now appears on the screen of right side and only appear in right side... but the images are being generated also on the center monitor\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-17T19:48:59Z\u0022 title=\u002203/17/2023 07:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by pmborg\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BeakyBuzz","CreatedById":225448,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-18T12:37:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs that normal, that with the following build and game settings, I only get ~30-40 FPS? Also, the GPU is constatnly above 70\u00B0C\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGigybyte Aorus Elite v2 -\u00A0 Ryzen 5600 -\u00A0RTX 3070 Ti - 16 Gb Ram (3200 Mhz) - M.2 1Tb SSD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.75\u0022 height=\u0022788\u0022 style=\u0022height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022AiK4vmr.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/AiK4vmr.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002283.06\u0022 height=\u0022996\u0022 style=\u0022height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u002221VwyzN.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/21VwyzN.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, is it just mine, or is this normal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-29T14:13:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224261623\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679143039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225448\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BeakyBuzz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/18/2023 at 7:37 AM, BeakyBuzz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESo, is it just mine, or is this normal?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeither. It\u0027s not just you and it\u0027s not normal, but it\u0027s what we\u0027ve got right now. Keep an eye on your framerate on the title screen as well. Mine jumped up to 550. Had to cap the rate to keep from frying my GPU.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, nice rig. Bought a new desktop (mostly for this game), but I still have my Aorus 17x. It\u0027s a 12 pound behemoth, but the thing\u0027s an animal. And I can\u0027t do without a mechanical keyboard now. Once you go clickety-clack, you never go back\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-14T21:54:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs patch 2 is now out, this is no longer relevant.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}